The paper focuses on the control and coordination of small military robots in a combat environment, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of autonomous and coordinated behaviors, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also considers the challenges of navigating complex environments, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY) or computer vision (cs.CV) if visual sensing is used.
